 HOW TO SEARCH FOR A VIRUS


    In  the  menu there is a function  which is called 'Global Search'
    (LEFT  AMIGA-G).   If  you  select this you will be presented by a
    small window with two string gadgets.
    
    Here  you  can  search  for strings within the files of the assign
    'Virus:'.   Lets say you would like to see all the descriptions of
    the  vira  which  are  very  dangerous.   First  you  write  'very
    dangerous'  into  the top string gadget.  You do not need to write
    anything  in  the bottom gadget but if you do both strings must be
    found  in a file before there is a match.  To search for something
    you MUST write something in the top gadget.
    
    After  this  type  of  search  has  ended and there were matches a
    window will pop up and show those descriptions, which matched with
    the  string(s)  you  entered.  You can now click on a name and you
    will  see the description in the text viewer.  If you click cancel
    you  will  not have to search for them again.  You can just choose
    'List  matches'  (LEFT  AMIGA-l) from the menu and the window with
    the matching descriptions will pop up again.

    If  you press the 'Search for name' gadget and it is activated you
    are searching for a file with exactly that name and not within the
    file.   The  bottom  string  gadget will then be ignored.

    If  a  description  with that name was found it will be loaded and
    shown in the text viewer.
@ENDNODE

